 VITE_API_URL=<api_url> 
#this is for only frontend docker container, it will be used to set the base URL for API calls in the frontend application. You can replace <api_url> with the actual URL of your backend API, such as http://localhost:8080/api or the appropriate URL if you are using Docker Compose with service names.
# for .env.k8s file just set it to /api because in Kubernetes, the frontend and backend services will be running in the same cluster, and the frontend can access the backend using the service name defined in your Kubernetes configuration.